File: Eskom consumers are urged to continue using electricity sparingly as load-shedding resumes. JOHANNESBURG - Load-shedding is back after two weeks of no outages. Eskom says it will implement Stage 1 load-shedding from 9am Monday morning until 11pm. READ: Eskom to implement Stage 1 load-shedding The utility warns the power outages could continue until Thursday. It says the move is to rebuild depleted emergency reserves and help meet rising electricity demand during the week. LOAD-SHEDDING: Schedules, info, and how it affects you Eskom says there’s been an increase in electricity demand since January, putting pressure on its ageing fleet. Consumers are urged to continue using electricity sparingly. What is Stage 1 load-shedding? Stage 1 requires the least amount of load-shedding (up to 1,000 MW) and can be implemented three times over a four-day period for two hours at a time, or three times over an eight-day period for 4 hours at a time.